description:
Disaster on the Potomac



Aired on 12/23/2013, Narrated by: Jonathan Aris



On 13 January 1982, Air Florida Flight 90 takes off from a snowy runway in Washington D.C, stalls at 300 feet altitude, strikes a road bridge and crashes into the Potomac River, killing a total of 78 people.
